# ============================================================================
# AZURE STATIC WEB APPS ENVIRONMENT CONFIGURATION
# ============================================================================
# Environment variables needed for Azure Functions to work properly
# ============================================================================

# EMAIL SERVICE CONFIGURATION FOR AZURE FUNCTIONS
# ============================================================================
# This must be set in Azure Static Web Apps Configuration (not in code!)
# Go to: Azure Portal > Your Static Web App > Configuration > Application Settings

# Primary email password variable (required)
HOSTINGER_EMAIL_PASSWORD=your-actual-hostinger-email-password

# Alternative email password variable (fallback)
EMAIL_PASSWORD=your-actual-hostinger-email-password

# Optional: Custom email API URL (if using external service)
# VITE_EMAIL_API_URL=https://your-custom-email-api.com

# ============================================================================
# AZURE STATIC WEB APPS CONFIGURATION INSTRUCTIONS:
# ============================================================================
#
# 1. Go to Azure Portal (portal.azure.com)
# 2. Navigate to your CareXPS Static Web App resource
# 3. Click on "Configuration" in the left sidebar
# 4. Under "Application settings", click "+ Add"
# 5. Add the following environment variables:
#
#    Name: HOSTINGER_EMAIL_PASSWORD
#    Value: [your actual Hostinger email password]
#
#    Name: EMAIL_PASSWORD
#    Value: [your actual Hostinger email password]
#
# 6. Click "Save" to apply the configuration
# 7. The Azure Functions will automatically restart with new environment variables
#
# ============================================================================
# TESTING THE EMAIL SERVICE:
# ============================================================================
#
# After deploying and configuring environment variables:
#
# 1. Open browser console on your deployed app
# 2. Run: sendQuickTestEmail('your-email@example.com')
# 3. Check for successful response and email delivery
# 4. If errors occur, check Azure Function logs in Application Insights
#
# ============================================================================
# TROUBLESHOOTING:
# ============================================================================
#
# If getting 503 errors:
# - Verify environment variables are set in Azure Portal
# - Check Azure Function logs in Application Insights
# - Ensure SMTP credentials are correct
# - Test with sendQuickTestEmail() function first
#
# If getting CORS errors:
# - Azure Functions now include proper CORS headers
# - Check network tab for actual error responses
#
# If emails not sending:
# - Verify Hostinger SMTP settings
# - Check email quota/limits
# - Verify sender email (carexps@phaetonai.com) is configured
#
# ============================================================================